properties.text: The priests who worshipped Balaan were called the Withered. They practiced death magic in order to ferry souls to the goddess of death.

While not being able to truly defeat the angels, with the help of the Withered Hand, the Bloodthorn Knights were able to banish them from Dissodia, locking them in within their angelic plane of existence.
Until the last, the Druidic Council of Three were unaware of Balaans true plan. If they did, they would have not gone along with it. Their ignorance cost them dearly.
With each godly death, their powerful souls were shepherded into the care of Balaan, strengthening her, and her cultists.
When all the woodland gods but Balaan and Thaea were destroyed, they came up with a plan, only to be enacted in the event of either ones death.
The Withered Hand were a small, secret sect of the Withered devoted to the unholy teachings of Balaan. They grew strong, as the other druidic gods perished.
Press E

When Castle Thornburg's King, and the goddess Thaea were betrayed by the Archangel Barthran, Castle Moss turned to the last of their woodland gods for help against Heaven's Point, Bal'aan. Risking all in order to survive... at a price.
Prior to the Assault on the Penitent Tower, Bronn Talstead, the leader of Castle Thornburgs Bloodthorn Knights, met with the Druidic Council of Castle Moss.

One by one, Heavens Point hunted down and eradicated the demi-gods worshipped by the people of Castle Moss for their assault on the Penitent Tower. A representative from Castle Thornburg was summoned to the Tower to answer for the rumors of their involvement. King Thornburg chose to plead his case to the Archangels himself.
Press E

The Archangels were Heavens chosen leaders on Dissodia. Led by Barthran, this small sect of the most powerful, and arrogant of angels ruled over the Penitent Tower, demanding respect from all living beings.
While most of the Withered practiced small forms of death magic, some close to Bal'aan dove into even darker magics, like necromancy.
With King Thornburgs death at the hands of Barthran, Bronn and his knights set out to stop the archangels once and for all.
Enchanted to secrecy by Balaan, Bronn and the Bloodthorns ruled over Castle Thornburg for twenty years until the Dwarf King-Of-War Baron bested him in single combat, winning the kingdom.
The druidic trickster goddess of death, Balaan, rivaled only her sister, Thaea, in power.
